reserve i for (Morphism of C);
theorem
(f is  retraction iff ( f opp ) is  coretraction)
proof
thus (f is  retraction implies ( f opp ) is  coretraction)
proof
given i such that
A1: ( cod i ) = ( dom f )
and
A2: ( f * i ) = ( id ( cod f ) );

take ( i opp );
thus ( dom ( i opp ) ) = ( dom f ) by A1,OPPCAT_1:8
.= ( cod ( f opp ) ) by OPPCAT_1:8;
thus ( ( i opp ) * ( f opp ) ) = ( ( id ( cod f ) ) opp ) by A1,A2,OPPCAT_1:16
.= ( id ( ( cod f ) opp ) ) by OPPCAT_1:20
.= ( id ( dom ( f opp ) ) ) by OPPCAT_1:10;
end;

given i being (Morphism of ( C opp )) such that
A3: ( dom i ) = ( cod ( f opp ) )
and
A4: ( i * ( f opp ) ) = ( id ( dom ( f opp ) ) );

take ( opp i );
thus A5: ( cod ( opp i ) ) = ( cod ( f opp ) ) by A3,OPPCAT_1:9
.= ( dom f ) by OPPCAT_1:8;
thus ( f * ( opp i ) ) = ( ( f * ( opp i ) ) opp ) by OPPCAT_1:def 4
.= ( ( ( opp i ) opp ) * ( f opp ) ) by A5,OPPCAT_1:16
.= ( id ( dom ( f opp ) ) ) by A4,OPPCAT_1:7
.= ( id ( ( cod f ) opp ) ) by OPPCAT_1:10
.= ( ( id ( cod f ) ) opp ) by OPPCAT_1:20
.= ( id ( cod f ) ) by OPPCAT_1:def 4;
end;
